Female ( Paratype ). Total length 8.0. Carapace 3.0 long, 2.6 wide. Eye sizes: ALE: 0.15 , PME: 0.15 , PLE: 0.13 . Clypeus equal in width to two and one­half diameters of PME. Distance between PME and PLE equal to 0.37 diameters of PME. PME separated from ALE by 1.4 diameters of former. Leg formula: II, IV, I, III. Leg I: femur 3.9 / patella 0.9 / tibia 3.8 / metatarsus 3.7 / tarsus 1.1 / total 13.4 / II: 4.2 / 0.9 / 4.2 / 4.3 / 1.1 / 14.7 / III: 3.6 / 0.9 / 3.1 / 3.6 / 0.9 / 12.1 / IV: 3.9 / 0.9 / 3.7 / 4.4 / 1.0 / 13.9 . Leg I 4.5 times as long as carapace. Femur I 1.3 times as long as carapace. Palpal tarsus not incrassate. Four tubular spermathecae, the internal ones having a curvature in the distal portion (
Fig. 5
). Colour pattern as in male, except the palpal tibia and tarsus, which are reddish brown.
